TopicTitle: Parts list flicker/editor HUD elements disappearing

Articles.Content:
54 minutes ago, Tr1gg3r said:

Ive managed to get the flicker without filter ext mod and kis kas, if i go over 60 parts in a category it strikes, hasnt made difference which mods tbh.

ive made thread in unmodded, 'bug i.d. Advice' feel free to keep bumping it til we get action

do you play in "popupwindow" -mode?

edit: nvm, thats not causing it :-/

Edited October 15, 2016 by Speadge

nah, im basic set up 1600x900, no force open gl or dx11 tricks or anything. I've managed to find combo of mods that dont seem to trigger UI bug, i'll edit this in bit with my list - (not motivated to play ksp atm)

What is FilterExtensions? I think this means I don't have it.

Yes, @RoverDude stream https://www.twitch.tv/roverdude/v/95003269 shows the effect at about 6 mins 30 seconds.

18 minutes ago, Kaa253 said:

What is FilterExtensions? I think this means I don't have it.

Yes, @RoverDude stream https://www.twitch.tv/roverdude/v/95003269 shows the effect at about 6 mins 30 seconds.

a mod, as it say, to add filters for several groups to the editor.

but thats not what causing it.

I split' my install/mods into 3 separate installdirs.

each install is working fine, but as soon as i copy the mods of one install to the other, it starts flickering - and just when copying part-mods.

16 minutes ago, Kaa253 said:

What is FilterExtensions? I think this means I don't have it.

Yes, @RoverDude stream https://www.twitch.tv/roverdude/v/95003269 shows the effect at about 6 mins 30 seconds.

filterextensions is a mod that i think allows you to create custom categories etc, ive never used it.

its not the cause anyhow if you do have/ get it.

i'll wait until it annoys the squad dev's enough that they look at it

ive asked what they want us to do about this in unmodded thread, but no answer, so im not wasting anymore of my life on it. lol
What OS is this seen it?  Windows only?

Getting this UI problem aswell as i cant seem to launch with 1.2-2 TWR, seems fine when i remove all the mods, i do have a number of them installed.

Hmm... some more investigation...

The "flickering" in the parts lists seems to actually be a layering error. While it "flickers" the background of the parts list, and the window border along the top of the screen moves in front of, and completely conceals, everything else. You can still see the Launch, Save, Open, etc buttons -behind- the top bar where they peek out beneath it.

The vanishing/flickering of the tray icons is not connected at all to the flickering in the parts list. The two can happen entirely separately, or together. However, context menus on the basic stock tools (contracts for example) are only blank while the mod tray is invisible, and have text when the mod tray is visible again. Possible DirectDraw error?

Changing to DX11 had no noticeable effect at all for me. If there's a difference, it's beyond my ability to detect.

It -seems- (though I'm having a heck of a time confirming this) that anything that uses the Unity skin is immune to the flickering... but things like Blizzy's toolbar don't flicker even if it's using the KSP skin, so I'm not sure. I can say for certain that nothing with the Unity skin flickers, but that may simply be a coincidence that only mods use the Unity skin, and none of the mods flicker (except for their icons in the stock AppLauncher tray). Still, it's enough to make me wonder if it may be a glitch in Unity having to do with using two skins simultaneously.
